      <h2>Best Secured Credit Cards in India</h2>
      <p>Secured credit cards are the perfect solution for individuals with no credit history, a low CIBIL score, or previous credit issues. Unlike regular cards, secured cards are backed by a fixed deposit (FD) with the issuing bank, which serves as collateral. Your credit limit is typically set at 80-90% of your FD value, and since the bank has security, approval is virtually guaranteed regardless of your creditworthiness.</p>
      <p>The best part? Secured cards are reported to credit bureaus just like regular credit cards. This means every on-time payment you make actively builds (or rebuilds) your CIBIL score. After 12-18 months of responsible usage, most banks will upgrade you to an unsecured card and release your FD — giving you a regular credit card with an improved credit score.</p>

      <h2>Key Features of Secured Credit Cards</h2>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Guaranteed Approval:</strong> No credit score check required — backed by your FD, approval is virtually assured</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Build Credit History:</strong> Every payment is reported to CIBIL, Experian, and Equifax — building your score from scratch</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Earn FD Interest:</strong> Your fixed deposit continues earning interest (6-7% p.a.) even while it serves as card collateral</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Upgrade Path:</strong> After 12-18 months of good usage, banks upgrade you to a regular unsecured card</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Full Card Benefits:</strong> Enjoy rewards, cashback, EMI options, and fuel surcharge waivers just like any other card</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Low FD Requirement:</strong> Start with an FD as low as ₹15,000-₹25,000 depending on the bank</li>
      </ul>

