      <h2>Eligibility for Secured Credit Cards</h2>
      <p>Secured cards have the most relaxed eligibility criteria of any credit card type:</p>

      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age:</strong> 18-70 years — the widest age range of any card category</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income:</strong> No minimum income requirement — the FD amount determines your credit limit</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Score:</strong> No minimum CIBIL score required; ideal for scores below 600 or no credit history</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Fixed Deposit:</strong> Must place an FD of ₹15,000-₹5,00,000 with the issuing bank as collateral</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment:</strong> Open to all — salaried, self-employed, students, homemakers, retired individuals</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Documents:</strong> PAN Card, Aadhaar Card, and FD receipt — minimal documentation required</li>
      </ul>

